# Portal Migration Walkthrough - Halo UI/UX

I have successfully migrated the sub-pages for all three portals (Admin, Teacher, and Student) to the Halo design system. This migration ensures a premium, cohesive experience across the entire platform.

## Key Changes

### 1. Standardized Layout
- All pages now utilize the [DashboardPageLayout](file:///d:/eclassroom_day2/frontend/src/components/layout/DashboardPageLayout.tsx#12-45) component.
- Consistent header structure with descriptive titles and subtitles.
- Action areas in the header for primary page functions.

### 2. Premium Card Aesthetic
- Replaced basic containers with premium [Card](file:///d:/eclassroom_day2/reference/components/admin/ParticipantModal.tsx#33-38) components.
- Added subtle gradients, shadows, and interactive hover states.
- Improved spacing and typography for better readability.

### 3. Student Portal Highlights
- **Dashboard**: Personal welcome with time-based greetings and a visual "Today's Pulse" progress tracker.
- **Classes**: Clear card-based schedule view with direct links to virtual classrooms.
- **Doubts**: Interactive tabbed feed for pending and resolved questions.
- **Profile**: Modern identity management with avatar fallback and secure-style read-only fields.
- **Study Plan**: Hierarchical day-by-day curriculum view with smooth expansion and completion status.

### 4. Code Quality & Consistency
- Resolved previous build/lint errors.
- Standardized UI component usage ([Badge](file:///d:/eclassroom_day2/reference/components/ui/badge.tsx#30-35), [Button](file:///d:/eclassroom_day2/reference/components/ui/button.tsx#38-43), `Avatar`, `Tabs`, [Select](file:///d:/eclassroom_day2/reference/components/ui/select.tsx#15-55)).
- Maintained existing API integrations and form logic (using Zod and React Hook Form).

